==Spanish==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[dicat]]'', present subjunctive form of ''[[dicere]]''

===Verb form===
'''diga'''

# Present subjunctive third person (or second person formal) singular form of ''[[decir]]'': may it/you say, may it/you tell; polite singular imperative: say, tell.
# way to say [[hello]] on the [[telephone]]
#: "Diga." ("Talk"); "Dígame." ("Talk to me.", "Say something to me.")

